'''Dan McCoy''' (born 1978) is an American comedian and an Emmy-winning writer<ref>{{cite web|title=The Daily Show With Jon Stewart - Awards & Nominations|url=http://www.emmys.com/shows/daily-show-jon-stewart|publisher=Academy of Television Arts & Sciences|accessdate=28 January 2014}}</ref>  for the news satire program ''[[The Daily Show|The Daily Show with Jon Stewart]]''.  He is the producer/co-host of the bad movie podcast [[The Flop House]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Berube|first=Chris|title=That Awful Film, Incredibly, Has a Following|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/01/nyregion/box-office-duds-have-a-following-too.html|accessdate=28 January 2014|newspaper=The New York Times|date=31 January 2013}}</ref> which he co-hosts with comedian [[Stuart Wellington]] and fellow ''Daily Show'' writer [[Elliott Kalan]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Griffith|first=Colin|title=Dan McCoy, Elliott Kalan, and Stuart Wellington discuss their three favorite episodes of The Flop House|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/dan-mccoy-elliott-kalan-and-stuart-wellington-disc-101333|accessdate=28 January 2014|newspaper=A.V. Club|date=28 August 2013}}</ref>   He is the creator and co-star (along with ''Daily Show'' writer Matt Koff) of the animated webseries 9 AM Meeting, which won an [[MTV]] development deal at the 2010 [[New York Television Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title=New York Television Festival|url=http://nytvf.com/newsletter_9-28-10.htm/|work=Newsletter and Awards 2010}}</ref>

McCoy is a 1996 graduate of [[Eureka High School (Illinois)|Eureka High School]] in [[Eureka, Illinois]].<ref>Arlene Franks, [http://www.pantagraph.com/wcj/news/full-story-eureka-s-dan-mccoy-hits-it-big-in/article_7fd39b04-47a6-11e1-ad25-001871e3ce6c.html "Eureka's Dan McCoy Hits It Big in New York,"] ''Woodford County Journal,'' Feb. 1, 2012.</ref>  He is also a member of the Earlham College (Richmond, IN) Class of 2000.

